Gombe State government, has allocated 1, 000 hectares of land for the taking off of its industrial park project. Also yesterday, Gombe State governor, Muhammadu Inuwa, toured the proposed site of the industrial park, located in Dadinkowa, Yamaltu/Deba council area of the state. Yahaya, had at different forums, hinted on the economic gains of the industrial park to the state if it finally takes off, saying that it would tap into the soon-to-be inaugurated Dadinkowa Hydro Electric project. The governor, who spoke during the inspection of the site yesterday, said the state government would soon begin the construction of the industrial park. According to him, 1,000 hectares of land has been allocated for the project, adding that he will do everything possible to see to the success of the project. The governor also disclosed that investors had already indicated interest with a view to investing when the park comes on stream. Yahaya, however called for the support and cooperation to ensure that the project becomes a reality. He added that when it is fully functional, the industrial park would provide job opportunities for the teeming youths in the state and the country at large.